1
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,960
These Japanese

2
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:39,479
trample on the international convention

3
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,640
and seize by trickery or force.

4
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:44,680
Someone has to stand up and speak out.

5
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,759
Many big businessmen have fled.

6
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:52,080
A wise man stays away from dangerous situations, as they say.

7
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,840
But Mr. Tian

8
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,759
single-handedly tries to resolve the crisis.

9
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,759
So,

10
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:02,800
he gets himself into such a mess.

11
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,680
Others don't understand him,

12
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:07,600
but I understand his pains.

13
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:12,600
Master.

14
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:17,280
Did Mr. Tian tell you all this?

15
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,160
He

16
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,160
can only talk to an old man like me

17
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,000
about his difficulties.

18
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,160
Okay, I've noted it all down.

19
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,920
Raincoats, daily chemicals.

20
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,040
Yes.

21
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,960
Thank you very much for your donation.

22
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,160
Okay, bye.

23
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,400
Sis.

24
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,000
The records of donations and funds

25
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,880
are all here.

26
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,840
Okay, thanks for your hard work.

27
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,320
Let me give you a hand.

28
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,040
Everyone must be exhausted.

29
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:56,040
Our preparation ends here.

30
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,160
I'll treat you all to plain noodles later.

31
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,200
Can I have two bowls?

32
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,560
Five bowls is no problem, you greedy cat.

33
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,010
Come.

34
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,640
Hurry up.

35
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,650
Just put it here.

36
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,100
Here, Sis, put it here.

37
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:07,960
There's nothing left outside, right?

38
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,760
No.

39
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,680
Intelligence agent! Catch the intelligence agent!

40
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,480
Catch the intelligence agent!

41
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,400
Miss!

42
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:22,000
Catch the intelligence agent!

43
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,079
Catch the intelligence agent!

44
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,200
Quick, call a rickshaw.

45
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,760
Chenxi, call a rickshaw!

46
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:28,480
Mrs. Meng!

47
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,200
Mr. Tian sent me to pick you up.

48
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:30,960
Get in quickly.

49
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,840
Qi!

50
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,160
Qi!

51
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,200
Mr. Tian.

52
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,820
How is she recovering?

53
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,640
Her wound is healing quite well.

54
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,240
Last night,

55
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,370
she even talked with me for a long time.

56
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,880
Have some breakfast.

57
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,560
Thank you.

58
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,720
Mr. Tian, have you had breakfast?

59
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,000
I have.

60
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,960
I didn't know

61
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,410
you've had Qi protecting us all along.

62
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,600
Thank you.

63
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,920
I told you

64
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,900
we knew each other before.

65
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,400
Your father was eight years older than me.

66
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,280
When he passed the provincial exam, I had just become a Xiucai.

67
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:06,000
We met once.

68
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,660
When he was the education inspector in Jiangsu,

69
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:13,320
I had just returned to Haiwen from the provincial normal school

70
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,000
to be the Director of the Education Bureau.

71
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,040
With just a letter for help,

72
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:19,320
he helped me get Haiwen

73
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,560
its first teaching fund.

74
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:25,840
Your father did me a great favor.

75
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,360
You fought in many battles and suffered injustice,

76
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:32,020
yet you still have the will to return home and resist the Japanese.

77
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,640
It's rare.

78
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,840
Mr. Fan.

79
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,409
I have never abandoned my duty.

80
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,120
Returning to my hometown this time,

81
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:43,850
only by devoting myself to the country can I comfort my late father.

82
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,480
Please.

83
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,820
Earlier this year,

84
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,960
the Japanese army began to invade the Haiwen county town.

85
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,290
The National Army also retreated.

86
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:59,040
I had to lead a few government staff members

87
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,250
and moved around until we got here.

88
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,080
Yutang is an ancient town

89
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:07,320
with honest people who have farmed and studied for generations.

90
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,440
Haiwen and Nuo Creek areas,

91
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:13,440
and even the situation in the whole of Jiangsu is generally similar.

92
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:18,320
The Japanese and puppet troops occupy various counties and major traffic routes.

93
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:21,680
Acting Provincial Chairman and Commander of the 89th Army,

94
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,920
Han Deqin,

95
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,930
nominally controls all counties,

96
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:28,440
but each county has its own local forces.

97
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,280
For example, here,

98
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,559
there are Ge Zhiyuan's troops.

99
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,000
Under such circumstances,

100
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,600
it's very easy to form local armed forces.

101
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,360
Yes.

102
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,159
Many squires and prominent families

103
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:41,960
have acquired their own militiamen and weapons.

104
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,280
Some people

105
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:47,200
are unwilling to hand over their homes.

106
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,760
Some want to take the opportunity to proclaim themselves kings.

107
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,960
A commander every three li,

108
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,120
a captain every five li.

109
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:56,160
They all claim to resist the Japanese, but have different backgrounds.

110
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,160
They don't even obey

111
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:59,840
the orders of the Administrative Office Director,

112
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,800
let alone an exiled magistrate like me.

113
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:06,920
I formed the Self-Defense Corps just to protect ourselves.

114
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,800
Right now, we have just over a hundred people,

115
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:13,170
divided into two teams, managed by Battalion Commander Li.

116
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,640
Judging from what I saw on the way here,

117
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,800
the Japanese army is actually in the county town,

118
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,800
with only a few dozen troops stationed.

119
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,200
The puppet troops don't dare to leave the county town easily either.

120
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,720
If our Yutang Self-Defense Corps

121
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,040
can join forces with the nearby guerrillas,

122
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:29,000
the Japanese wouldn't dare to come down to the villages easily.

123
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,120
Yunkui.

124
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,960
I am old,

125
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:36,720
and no longer have the ability to expand the Self-Defense Corps.

126
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,400
We are but lowly officials in the state and county,

127
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:44,240
yet every branch and leaf reflects our concern.

128
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,280
Actually, as soon as I entered the hall,

129
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,400
I saw this couplet.

130
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,600
It reminded me of last August,

131
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,160
when I went to the Shanghai battlefield.

132
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,040
My father

133
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:58,250
also personally wrote this poem and gave it to me.

134
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,280
But it's a real pity

135
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,040
that it was destroyed on the Shanghai battlefield.

136
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:03,680
So,

137
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,800
when I saw this couplet,

138
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,200
I felt an inexplicable sense of intimacy.

139
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,800
I feel like you are my father.

140
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:15,480
Yunkui,

141
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:21,320
Although this is your ancestral home,

142
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,080
you grew up in Nanjing.

143
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,440
No one here knows you anymore.

144
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:29,240
But the situation in Haiwen

145
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,480
is still quite complicated.

146
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:34,240
You'd better change your name.

147
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:38,620
Since you want to mobilize everyone to fight the Japanese,

148
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,800
how about changing it to Dougui?

149
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,520
I crawled out from a pile of corpses.

150
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,880
Returning to Haiwen,

151
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,400
I also want to start anew.

152
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,440
Fight the Japanese, Dougui.

153
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,120
Zhang Dougui.

154
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:57,840
Okay, Mr. Fan.

155
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,760
I will use this name from now on.

156
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,760
Alright. Militia Commander of Haiwen,

157
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,080
you'll take on this role starting today.

158
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,490
I'm flattered, Mr. Fan.

159
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,600
It's good enough that you took us in.

160
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,080
Commander Zhang Dougui,

161
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:12,760
I hope you can lead the Haiwen Militia

162
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:16,280
to strategize and resist foreign invasion.

163
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,160
Let's go.

164
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,120
I'll show you around Haiwen.

165
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,120
Okay.

166
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,120
Haiwen has fallen.

167
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,720
Heroes refuse to live under the Japanese flag,

168
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:35,410
so even bandits have turned into guerrillas.

169
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:38,400
The bandits here have their own philosophy:

170
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,680
act righteously.

171
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,400
But when the Japanese came,

172
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,520
they found it shameful to be bandits.

173
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,720
In the early days of the occupation,

174
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,200
almost every month,

175
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,440
there was sensational news

176
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:54,040
that someone formed a guerrilla force in some village.

177
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,440
Some had a few guns, others had dozens.

178
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,200
Some were supported by the Communist Party,

179
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,720
some by the KMT,

180
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,330
and some acted on their own.

181
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,240
Wait a minute.

182
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,640
In Gejialou Village, where we're heading,

183
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,200
most of the villagers

184
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,120
have the surname Ge.

185
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:11,280
The 18th Detachment is the largest guerrilla force

186
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,920
in this area.

187
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,220
It has about a hundred men.

188
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,840
The 18th Detachment.

189
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,040
How big must this army be?

190
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:19,960
Where is the headquarters?

191
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,420
There's no headquarters.

192
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,920
I haven't even heard of

193
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,200
the 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 16th, or 17th.

194
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,360
They just started right at the 18th?

195
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,360
It's like looking back, I cannot see the ancients,

196
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,960
looking forward, I cannot see the comers.

197
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,600
From the commander to the deputy commander,

198
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,360
the chief of staff, down to the lowest soldier,

199
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,960
everyone from top to bottom, inside and out,

200
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,960
are relatives of the Ge family.

201
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:38,890
You're here.

202
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:39,840
Yes.

203
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,160
There are also tenants of the Ge family.

204
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:45,200
Those guns and bullets

205
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:48,480
were bought by wealthy families who sold their houses and land.

206
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,800
Ge Zhancheng's family sold the most land.

207
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,920
He used to be in the Beiyang Army,

208
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:56,640
so everyone elected him as the commander-in-chief.

209
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,400
Did you see that?

210
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,720
Those gathering firewood, collecting manure,

211
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:03,520
and those smoking pipes and sunbathing over there

212
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,920
are all guerrillas of the 18th Detachment.

213
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,560
Look here.

214
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,560
3,000 Japanese killed here.

215
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,680
Was there ever such a big battle here?

216
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,080
Why haven't I heard of it?

217
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,960
Right beneath this wall, the Japanese

218
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,720
killed three of our men.

219
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,720
That night, someone wrote on the wall:

220
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,400
'3 Japanese killed here'.

221
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,770
When guerrillas passed by,

222
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:29,120
the captain changed the words to:

223
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:32,640
'30 Japanese killed here'.

224
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,680
Since then,

225
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,880
whenever guerrillas pass by,

226
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:39,560
they change the numbers into hundreds or thousands.

227
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,880
If you ask me, that's still too slow.

228
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,840
Might as well change it to 30,000.

229
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,820
Killing 30,000 Japanese at once,

230
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,540
now that would be satisfying.

231
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,080
Do you think our 18th Detachment

232
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,900
only has a few broken guns?

233
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:58,140
They really think they are the Heroes of Liangshan.

234
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,320
In the end, they won't kill many Japanese.

235
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:03,090
They will just bring them here.

236
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,880
If they retaliate.

237
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:08,440
It will really become a disaster for the people.

238
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:11,040
All right, listen to my advice.

239
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:14,160
Don't provoke the Japs for nothing.

240
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,360
One Dot.

241
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,480
Pong.

242
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:19,840
Tell me.

243
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:22,520
Did we provoke the Japs?

244
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,880
Besides, it's almost the autumn harvest.

245
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,120
If they come again.

246
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,960
Are we supposed to sit and wait to die?

247
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,200
Let them come.

248
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:33,330
At worst, we'll leave them an empty town and village.

249
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:37,720
Strengthen the defenses, clear the fields, and carry out the scorched-earth policy.

250
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,760
White Dragon.

251
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:40,160
What is this?

252
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,680
These are all newly made.

253
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,200
Liuzi, what are you doing?

254
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,640
My food. My food.

255
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,640
I just steamed this.

256
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:48,300
It looks like pig slop. Is this for people to eat?

257
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,560
What are you doing?

258
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:52,520
Liuzi, don't think just because you have a gun now.

259
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:53,840
You can be so arrogant.

260
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,680
Did you forget you used to steal pancakes from our house?

261
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,280
What are you yelling about?

262
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,120
I'm telling you, not only will I smash it.

263
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,080
If you keep yelling.

264
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,280
I'll hit you.

265
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:02,720
Liuzi.

266
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,720
Don't fight.

267
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,200
Our commander has three rules for not fighting.

268
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,920
First, don't fight the Japanese cavalry.

269
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:13,040
The cavalry has six legs, and we have two.

270
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,180
We can't beat them.

271
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:15,560
Five Character.

272
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,720
Second, don't fight the puppet army.

273
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:18,930
Four Bamboo.

274
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:19,800
That's right.

275
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,880
The Ge surname is a big one.

276
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,440
It's inevitable to have old friends and relatives who defected to the enemy.

277
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:28,040
We Chinese shouldn't fight Chinese, right?

278
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,130
Nine Bamboo.

279
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:29,800
Pong.

280
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:31,640
Third.

281
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,680
Don't fight in the village.

282
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,960
This is to prevent the Japs.

283
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,880
From harming our people.

284
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,840
We still protect the people.

285
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:42,970
You say you want to protect the people.

286
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,660
But aren't you bullying them just like the Japs?

287
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:46,920
I...

288
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:49,000
Second Brother, sit.

289
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,280
Third Uncle Ge.

290
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:59,400
What you're saying doesn't make sense.

291
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:02,400
Look, we sold a hundred acres of good farmland.

292
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,360
For guns and bullets.

293
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,360
Isn't it for the War of Resistance?

294
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,840
Generalissimo Chiang said.

295
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:11,800
Those with money contribute money, those with strength contribute strength.

296
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,840
We asked you to bring some stuff. Is this edible?

297
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,560
How are we supposed to fight?

298
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:19,520
There's also a troop stationed in Qingshan Town.

299
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,880
They eat whatever the people give them.

300
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,960
Yeah, they even help grind the grain.

301
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,840
Fetch water, and plant crops.

302
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,800
How come people with the same surname are so overbearing?

303
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:28,840
Worse than those with different surnames?

304
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,040
All right, all right.

305
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,320
You're talking about the New Fourth Army, right?

306
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:34,180
I don't know about anything else.

307
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,760
They just like to sing.

308
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:39,660
They teach people to sing everywhere in the fields.

309
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,800
What are you doing?

310
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:43,800
And there are also girls with short hair.

311
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,880
Waving their arms and leading the singing,

312
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,720
claiming to promote the anti-Japanese resistance.

313
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:52,440
In fact, everyone just came to see the girls.

314
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:55,200
Who's in the mood for resistance?

315
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,480
Enough talk. Before noon,

316
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:01,440
stew your chickens and ducks

317
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,400
and bring them over.

318
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,000
Well...

319
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,040
Let's go.

320
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:05,560
Go, go, go.

321
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:08,640
Unruly mob.

322
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:10,560
Report!

323
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,960
Magistrate Fan and Commander Zhang Dougui are here to visit.

324
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,319
Who is Zhang Dougui?

325
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:19,920
I don't know.

326
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,599
My humble surname...

327
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:22,839
Yes.

328
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,280
Wanfu.

329
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:12,880
Why are you up here?

330
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:14,680
Sibao is not feeling well.

331
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:17,080
I'm here to bring Master his afternoon tea.

332
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:25,960
Give it to me.

333
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,890
What are you looking at?

334
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:32,960
Go back.

335
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,330
What's wrong with Mr. Tian?

336
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,280
Doesn't Master have neurasthenia?

337
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:40,560
His old illness is acting up,

338
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:41,840
and he has a migraine.

339
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:44,490
Right now, he's sensitive to sound and light.

340
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:45,520
Not to mention you,

341
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:48,050
even I can't just go in casually, understand?

342
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,600
Then why is my wife inside?

343
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:52,680
Isn't that because Mrs. Meng is by his side,

344
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:53,800
reading softly

345
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,840
to distract Master

346
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,800
and relieve his headache?

347
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,320
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

348
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:07,240
What kind of illness is this? It's so bizarre.

349
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,720
Don't worry about it.

350
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:28,370
Magistrate Fan.

351
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,400
When the Japanese came to Yutang Town,

352
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:31,480
did the 18th Detachment

353
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,240
really, as Ge Zhancheng said,

354
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:34,520
fight a tough battle?

355
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,760
To be honest, it's shameful.

356
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:41,840
The Japanese only sent a dozen men and one machine gun.

357
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:43,840
In all the surrounding miles,

358
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,040
not a single guerrilla force showed up.

359
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,280
They all took the elderly and children

360
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,210
and ran into the mountain gullies.

361
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,130
Are you very disappointed with this trip?

362
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,880
More than disappointed.

363
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,720
It's simply pathetic.

364
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,180
I seem to see a plate of loose sand.

365
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:01,840
They remind me of

366
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,760
the characters in Lu Xun's writings.

367
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:05,240
Ignorant and foolish.

368
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,000
Hastily formed a team,

369
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,880
and suddenly felt they

370
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,340
had the power to override the common people.

371
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:15,120
Internally blindly arrogant and hated,

372
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:17,160
externally having no fighting will at all.

373
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,280
Such a team

374
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:19,600
cannot win a battle.

375
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,640
In their hearts,

376
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:24,600
worldly wisdom and patriarchal etiquette

377
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,570
are greater than national hatred.

378
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,720
But thinking about it the other way round,

379
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:34,200
is there another reason here?

380
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:35,690
What do you mean?

381
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,880
For example, Ge Zhancheng always says

382
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:40,520
his life hobbies are only three hits.

383
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,090
Hitting his concubine,

384
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,240
playing mahjong, and fighting the Japs.

385
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:47,520
Now he has quit the first two,

386
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:50,080
and only focuses on fighting the Japanese.

387
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:54,400
But he doesn't know how to fight.

388
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,160
Let's go take a look by the river.

389
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,240
Okay.

390
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,970
Have you ever seen a house built with sand?

391
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,940
You can't build a house with sand.

392
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:13,320
Sand doesn't hold its shape.

393
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:16,240
But once it's mixed with cement,

394
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,680
it becomes cohesive.

395
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,240
Put bamboo strips and iron wire inside.

396
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,480
Whether you're building a wall

397
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,920
or a house,

398
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:27,200
you can build whatever you want.

399
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:29,180
It's stronger than anything.

400
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,800
This pile of loose sand in front of you

401
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,800
just needs a little cement as a binder.

402
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:40,440
If you can win them over,

403
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,920
you can mold this loose sand into a solid force,

404
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:46,040
turning farmers and wanderers

405
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:49,040
into organized warriors.

406
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:55,360
Uniting people's hearts is not an easy task.

407
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,880
I know.

408
00:21:57,440 --> 00:22:01,840
You've suffered many setbacks, felt lost and depressed.

409
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:05,880
But this is the place for you to show your worth.

410
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:10,360
Everything in the past died yesterday.

411
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:14,120
Everything in the future is born today.

412
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,960
This is a body reborn in righteousness.

413
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,570
Magistrate Fan.

414
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,520
What you just said

415
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,160
reminds me of my father.

416
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,240
I am honored.

417
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:01,560
East of the Yangtze is full of talented and spirited young men.

418
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:05,160
It's hard to say if they will make a comeback.

419
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,880
That's true.

420
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:53,960
Why are you sitting there?

421
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,040
I'm looking at the moon.

422
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,760
I miss Xiaoyue.

423
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,400
Wuhan has fallen.

424
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,800
I don't know her situation there.

425
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,440
I want to go find her.

426
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,800
Xiaoyue is just a girl.

427
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:34,480
You should go find her.

428
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:35,600
If you two are together,

429
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,480
at least you can look after each other.

430
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:40,560
But with the war like this,

431
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:43,600
I don't even know if I can go.

432
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:46,450
I have to take a boat to Hong Kong first,

433
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:49,160
then from Hong Kong to Guangzhou,

434
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,520
and Guangzhou to Wuhan.

435
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,400
Let alone Wuhan,

436
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,240
now Guangzhou has fallen too.

437
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,760
How can you go to Wuhan?

438
00:24:57,760 --> 00:24:59,080
Then what should I do?

439
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,580
Does that mean I'll never see Xiaoyue again?

440
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:04,520
I think

441
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:06,520
if you really want to go to Wuhan,

442
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:08,210
you might as well wait a bit.

443
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:10,880
Wait until the war stabilizes a bit before you go.

444
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:14,080
When you leave, if you don't have enough travel expenses,

445
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,810
I'll find a way to get it for you.

446
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:18,000
If I leave,

447
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,250
what about you guys?

448
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,360
You don't need to worry about us.

449
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,720
I have hands and feet.

450
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:26,290
I can definitely support Master and Yueming.

451
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:29,080
Don't think too much.

452
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,360
At least by Xiaoyue's side,

453
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:34,160
aren't Miss Yu and the Yu family there?

454
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,680
But the Japanese bombs don't have eyes.

455
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,200
When they drop bombs,

456
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:38,920
they can't tell

457
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:40,920
who is Her Ladyship and who is a maid.

458
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:42,760
What if they bomb our Xiaoyue?

459
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,600
You're thousands of li away.

460
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,760
If you insist on thinking like this,

461
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:47,620
aren't you just splitting hairs?

462
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,460
Why are you scaring yourself?

463
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:52,600
We have to look on the bright side.

464
00:25:52,680 --> 00:25:53,720
Don't you agree?

465
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:15,720
If our brigade commander were here,

466
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:18,040
how would you live

467
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,280
in Shanghai?

468
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,600
How else?

469
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,080
Like an ordinary family.

470
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:27,200
We'd just live peacefully.

471
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:33,000
Would you also read to our brigade commander

472
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,760
until midnight?

473
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:42,760
What do you mean by that?

474
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:44,920
I... It's nothing.

475
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:48,200
I'm just saying whatever comes to mind.

476
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:49,480
I just thought,

477
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:52,170
would you also read to our brigade commander?

478
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,720
Read in the morning, read in the afternoon.

479
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,960
Read in the afternoon, read in the evening.

480
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:58,280
I... I also thought our brigade commander

481
00:26:58,280 --> 00:27:00,120
would sing to you?

482
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:04,000
With his voice, and out of tune too.

483
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:05,360
I don't even like listening to it.

484
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,520
Are you okay?

485
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,320
I'm fine.

486
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:12,600
If you're fine, go wash up and sleep early.

487
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,680
Look at the moon.

488
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:14,760
I'm tired.

489
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,410
Aren't you leaving?

490
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,860
I'll miss Xiaoyue for a while longer.

491
00:27:58,360 --> 00:27:59,640
Look at Yutang Town.

492
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,720
The people have fled,

493
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,320
and the land is deserted.

494
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:06,120
It's planting season now.

495
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,400
If we don't plant,

496
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:10,720
there will be no harvest next year.

497
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,480
I've been trying to persuade the villagers to come back and farm.

498
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,740
But the guerrillas in the mountains said

499
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:18,680
that the crops would just go to the Japanese anyway,

500
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,210
so it's better not to plant.

501
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:22,720
They even said we will fight to the last man,

502
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,600
let the land be deserted.

503
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,000
But they never thought about

504
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,680
who will supply the guerrillas

505
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:30,320
after the land is destroyed.

506
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,600
According to the theory of guerrilla warfare,

507
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:39,730
the guerrillas are the fish and the people are the water.

508
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:44,240
But how long can the fish survive on this scorched earth?

509
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:47,120
If the people don't want to farm,

510
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,440
we can help them.

511
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:49,400
For one thing,

512
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,840
we can lighten the burden on the people.

513
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:53,240
Secondly, we can cultivate and reclaim wasteland.

514
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:55,320
We have the time besides training.

515
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,560
That's great.

516
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:05,360
Here.

517
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:09,960
Thank you.

518
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,260
Who asked you to carry so much?

519
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,760
No one asked her to. We couldn't stop her.

520
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:16,800
I wanted to carry it myself.

521
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:17,720
You guys only know how to bully people.

522
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:18,960
Take your things back.

523
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,160
It's nothing. I can carry it.

524
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:20,760
I can do it.

525
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:21,360
Why did you poke me?

526
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:21,960
It's okay.

527
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:22,960
Didn't you ask Xiaoyue to carry it?

528
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:24,240
You shouldn't be doing this.

529
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,080
How can you do this?

530
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:26,480
It's okay. I'm used to it.

531
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,280
It's nothing.

532
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,120
I won't let you carry it.

533
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:29,000
I can carry it,

534
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:29,600
right?

535
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:30,840
Who told you to carry this?

536
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:31,400
I got it.

537
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:31,920
No one asked you to carry it.

538
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,040
You always do this.

539
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:40,720
I was right about bringing a bamboo hat.

540
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,080
This is how Yutang Town is.

541
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:42,720
You'll get used to it.

542
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:43,720
Xiaoyue is smart.

543
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,940
She even brought an umbrella.

544
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,520
Battalion Commander Li,

545
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,120
why is there a vehicle there?

546
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,720
There was a battle here before.

547
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,560
The engine of that car was severely damaged.

548
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:01,000
We didn't know how to fix it,

549
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,330
so we just left it there.

550
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:03,880
I'll go take a look.

551
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:04,480
Okay.

552
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:05,540
I'll go too.

553
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:07,200
Come, show them around.

554
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,440
Okay, this way.

555
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:21,450
The chickens laid eggs too.

556
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,120
Battalion Commander Li,

557
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:31,250
where's the engine?

558
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,200
What about the Township Office?

559
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:36,920
Good stuff.

560
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:43,440
My dear Sis with a round face,

561
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:47,280
her mouth is so cute.

562
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:51,000
A little cherry mouth, oh my.

563
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:55,200
I love her to death, call her Sister-in-law.

564
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:59,000
My dear Sis with a round face,

565
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:02,840
her mouth is so cute.

566
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,640
A little cherry mouth, oh my.

567
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,490
Stop working and eat first.

568
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,240
Time to eat.

569
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:11,480
Coming.

570
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:18,560
Time to eat.

571
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:21,760
Come on, brothers. Hurry up.

572
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:22,720
Time to eat.

573
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,490
Brother Zhang, time to eat.

574
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,160
Miss Xiaoyue,

575
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,200
what delicious food did you bring?

576
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:32,400
Steamed flour rolls.

577
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:36,200
Brother Zhang, drink some water.

578
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:36,800
Thank you.

579
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,240
Okay.

580
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:38,920
Come on.

581
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,640
Xiaoyue, Xiaoyue.

582
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:06,960
Miss Xiaoyue,

583
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,600
have you learned how to grow crops before?

584
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,680
Before my parents and I fled from famine,

585
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,040
we used to farm at home.

586
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:14,240
My father said

587
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:17,210
this compost is the best and most fragrant thing.

588
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:20,560
Mountain peaks and riverbeds, places without plowing or planting,

589
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:22,220
don't have this smell of dirt.

590
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:25,040
I still remember when I was young,

591
00:32:25,080 --> 00:32:26,880
going to the town with my father.

592
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,120
We passed by a restaurant

593
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:32,560
and smelled a meaty aroma.

594
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:34,360
I couldn't help but

595
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:36,200
sniff constantly.

596
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,740
How could there be such a fragrant smell?

597
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,920
It smells so good.

598
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:42,610
Then my father came over

599
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:43,650
and glared at me.

600
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,440
He said, 'What's so good about this smell?

601
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:47,500
Can it be as fragrant as our compost?'

602
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:57,720
My father said a real farmer

603
00:32:57,880 --> 00:32:59,120
sees crops

604
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:01,160
just like seeing his own children,

605
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:04,160
feeling heartache and love from the bottom of his heart.

606
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:07,880
But such a skilled farmer

607
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:11,280
starved to death.

608
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:03,160
This fertilizer,

609
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,280
you have to wait for it to dry completely,

610
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,480
then crush it.

611
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,929
Sprinkle it on the crops like this,

612
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:11,440
so they can grow vigorously.

613
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:22,530
Come, I'll teach you how to sprinkle fertilizer.

614
00:34:25,679 --> 00:34:26,480
Like this,

615
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:29,320
throw it out.

616
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:37,120
Yueming,

617
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:40,280
Haiwen, Jiangsu is your ancestral home,

618
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:42,960
where your grandfather grew up.

619
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:44,960
Your father Yunkui

620
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,639
brought Auntie Xiaoyue,

621
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:49,120
Uncle You, and others back here.

622
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:53,239
At that time, most parts of Jiangsu Province

623
00:34:53,239 --> 00:34:56,100
were controlled or occupied by Japanese invaders.

624
00:34:56,679 --> 00:34:59,320
The homeland fell into enemy hands.

625
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:02,800
The people's cries for salvation rose one after another,

626
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:06,680
but they lacked a core force to unite all sides.

627
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:11,200
Facing the complex environment, your father Yunkui

628
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:15,320
insisted on developing anti-Japanese guerrilla forces behind enemy lines.

629
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,080
He led people in military training,

630
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:19,480
reclaiming wasteland, and growing crops,

631
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:22,080
setting his feet on this

632
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,280
solid land.

633
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:36,370
It's really getting better day by day.

634
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:38,560
Does it hurt when you pull the wound?

635
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:39,800
Much better.

636
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,400
Okay.

637
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:42,860
I'll try it myself.

638
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,400
Okay, take it easy.

639
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:46,600
No problem.

640
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:19,560
Mr. Tian is here.

641
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:21,160
Mr. Tian.

642
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:23,880
You're getting better day by day.

643
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:26,360
I can even walk around. Thank you.

644
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:27,570
That's good.

645
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:30,010
It's a pity that you can't leave this room,

646
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:31,700
and can only move around here.

647
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:33,120
Come on, have lunch.

648
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,040
Thank you.

649
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,600
Have you read the news?

650
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:49,000
I showed the newspaper to Sister Zeng.

651
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,520
Many of my friends saw this news

652
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,200
and were deeply distressed.

653
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:55,520
One of them has a strong sense of justice

654
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:58,760
and has always insisted on fighting to the end.

655
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:01,720
After reading it, he came to my place and cried his eyes out.

656
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,200
He said that a founding father of the National Revolution,

657
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,960
the most charismatic political leader,

658
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:07,040
just betrayed the party and the country like this.

659
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:12,200
He asked where the future of the anti-Japanese war lies

660
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:15,090
and if we have any chance of winning at all.

661
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:19,280
Then how did you comfort him, Mr. Tian?

662
00:37:20,120 --> 00:37:21,520
I couldn't comfort him.

663
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,960
Because I share the same confusion.

664
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:31,440
I wonder what your views are, Ms. Zeng.

665
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,320
I know

666
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:36,680
what you think of people like me.

667
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:39,680
You call it the weakness

668
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,490
and compromise of the national bourgeoisie.

669
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:47,280
Mr. Tian, you deliberately hid your revolutionary nature.

670
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,920
To be honest, Mr. Tian,

671
00:37:50,080 --> 00:37:51,760
You took a great risk

672
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:53,280
to save and cover for me.

673
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,640
My gratitude is beyond words.

674
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:58,720
If anything I say next is inappropriate,

675
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:01,080
you can refute me at any time.

676
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:02,780
I'm asking for advice.

677
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:11,800
Actually, Wang Jingwei's defection is not surprising.

678
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,400
The Anti-Japanese War has entered a stalemate phase.

679
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:19,320
Economic difficulties and traitors' disruptions

680
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:22,320
will be two major problems that persist in the future.

681
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:25,720
There is a saying popular all over the country now,

682
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:31,360
'Fight to the end, hold on and wait for a change.'

683
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:35,400
'Hold on and wait for a change,' Hu Shih said.

684
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:36,600
But

685
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:39,280
where exactly is the bottom line of the war?

686
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,800
What is the change in 'holding on and waiting for a change'?

687
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:44,930
Different people must have different understandings.

688
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:46,960
For people like Wang Jingwei,

689
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:50,600
his bottom line is China's major cities.

690
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,770
With all major cities lost,

691
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,920
he felt there was no way out.

692
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:58,120
They were waiting for the Japanese invaders to change their attitude.

693
00:38:58,120 --> 00:39:00,760
Once the Japanese invaders waved to negotiate,

694
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:03,280
he immediately ran over and became a traitor.

695
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:05,560
Then Mr. Chiang's bottom line

696
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:09,280
is waiting for Europe and America to change their attitudes.

697
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:11,960
Then in Mr. Tian's heart,

698
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,720
what is the bottom line of the war?

699
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,560
And what are you waiting for?

700
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:21,640
I know

701
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:25,400
you have done a lot of practical things for the war.

702
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,960
Besides donating money and materials,

703
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:32,170
your factory in the concession continues to produce

704
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,760
to meet the people's livelihood.

705
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,800
You also fight against the Japanese invaders for

706
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,560
the factories in the occupied areas.

707
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:42,600
I did that for money. It's asking a tiger for its skin.

708
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:48,360
I probably know a bit more than Yujiao.

709
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:51,040
I know that many workers in your factory

710
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:54,280
have joined the anti-Japanese forces.

711
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:55,520
I also know

712
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:59,440
at least one factory manager went to Yan'an.

713
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:02,610
Coincidentally, I handled it.

714
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:07,760
He told me you gave him 2,000 yuan for travel expenses.

715
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:09,720
You knew where he was going, but you didn't point it out.

716
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:12,320
This is a tacit understanding between you two.

717
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:16,440
Actually, I didn't say that much to him.

718
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,810
I did give him travel expenses.

719
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:22,160
Later, he did go to Yan'an.

720
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:26,320
Actually, I'm saying this

721
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:29,000
not just to praise you.

722
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,360
I want to say that

723
00:40:31,120 --> 00:40:33,320
although you have done a lot for the war,

724
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:35,760
you still don't know where the future lies.

725
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,360
You are still confused inside.

726
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,080
Just like some big businessmen,

727
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:41,080
they let one child join the KMT,

728
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:43,120
one child join the Communist Party,

729
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:44,000
one go abroad,

730
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,810
and one deal with the Japanese.

731
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,800
From a personal and family perspective,

732
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,600
it actually more fully proves

733
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:51,120
their inner confusion.

734
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:55,800
Yes, it's a pity I don't have children.

735
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:59,320
But my heart is just like theirs,

736
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:01,840
full of confusion.

737
00:41:02,480 --> 00:41:05,880
Actually, the path Mr. Tian is taking is harder.

738
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:08,920
It's asking a tiger for its skin.

739
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,920
Fight for a point, gain a point.

740
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,200
So fighting for it is beneficial to the war.

741
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:18,340
Otherwise, it's beneficial to the Japanese invaders.

742
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:20,760
Have you thought about it? For now,

743
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,120
this path is getting narrower and narrower.

744
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:26,320
Giving up halfway means all previous efforts are wasted.

745
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,160
If you continue,

746
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:30,530
I'm afraid you not only won't succeed,

747
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:32,920
but will be hurt by the tiger.

748
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,720
Mr. Tian relies on International Law

749
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:40,640
and the concession authorities.

750
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:41,400
But have you ever thought that

751
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:43,600
if the war expands one day

752
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:46,000
and Britain and the US are dragged into it,

753
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:48,040
the concession will cease to exist?

754
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:49,660
How will everything you do

755
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,880
be put into practice?

756
00:41:56,200 --> 00:41:57,280
I have.

757
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:03,160
Do you have any suggestions, Ms. Zeng?

758
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:06,200
Actually, I know Mr. Tian

759
00:42:07,520 --> 00:42:10,200
must have been working on a new plan.

760
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:11,960
Right?

761
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:17,800
May I ask,

762
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:23,920
what is the Communist Party's bottom line for the resistance?

763
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:26,490
Are you also expecting something?

764
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:28,250
Are you waiting for something?

765
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:30,770
In my personal understanding,

766
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:34,020
the bottom line of the resistance

767
00:42:34,480 --> 00:42:37,040
should be our 450 million compatriots,

768
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:39,960
whose hearts refuse to be enslaved.

769
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:44,880
I can see it from every person

770
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:47,320
who donates to the resistance with hopeful eyes.

771
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:49,560
From the angry eyes of everyone

772
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,120
bullied by the Japanese,

773
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:53,240
I can feel that tremendous power.

774
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,280
That is exactly what we seek

775
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:56,560
and what we expect.

776
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:59,250
The awakening of the whole nation.

777
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:04,120
The awakening and cohesion of every heart.
